A Cash-in-Transit van was robbed on Ontdekkers Road in Roodepoort, on Tuesday evening. News, Accidents, Robberies & Incidents reported on its Facebook page that multiple response teams were dispatched to assist at the scene as the armed robbers were still engaged in gunfire. A G4S Cash-in-Transit vehicle was blown up between CR Swart Drive and Corlett Avenue on Ontdekkers Road.  According to reports from Intellidrive, security guards were injured and the suspects managed to evade arrest and escape. A manhunt is still under way.